# Copy to .env and fill in
FASTAPI_URL=http://localhost:8000
WA_SERVICE_PORT=3001
LUCID_WA_NUMBER=919995265115

# Ownership is NOT configured here. Lucid's number is public — anyone can message
# it — so a chat may only write to the archive after it proves it owns the number:
# /connectors issues a one-time code, the user sends it to Lucid, and the backend
# binds that chat as owner (stored in backend/whatsapp_config.json).
# Until someone pairs, WhatsApp ingest stays closed and archives nothing.

# Production (see DEPLOYMENT.md). On ARM hosts (Oracle Ampere) Puppeteer's bundled
# Chromium is x86-only and will not start — install chromium-browser and point here.
# PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH=/usr/bin/chromium-browser

# Persist the WhatsApp session across restarts. Lose this and the account unlinks,
# forcing a QR re-scan on every deploy.
# WA_AUTH_PATH=/var/lib/lucid/wwebjs_auth

# /send has no auth — keep the bridge on loopback. Defaults to 127.0.0.1.
# WA_SERVICE_HOST=127.0.0.1
